\subtree{
\title{Configuring TLS 1.3 for Secure Communications}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{TLS 1.3 (RFC 8446) is the latest version of the Transport Layer Security protocol, providing significant improvements over TLS 1.2 in both security and performance. It reduces handshake latency to 1-RTT (and 0-RTT for resumed sessions), removes obsolete cipher suites, and mandates perfect forward secrecy. This skill covers configuring TLS 1.3 on servers, validating configurations, and testing for common misconfigurations.}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use}
\ul{
\li{When deploying or configuring configuring tls 1 3 for secure communications capabilities in your environment}
\li{When establishing security controls aligned to compliance requirements}
\li{When building or improving security architecture for this domain}
\li{When conducting security assessments that require this implementation}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Prerequisites}
\ul{
\li{Familiarity with cryptography concepts and tools}
\li{Access to a test or lab environment for safe execution}
\li{Python 3.8+ with required dependencies installed}
\li{Appropriate authorization for any testing activities}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Objectives}
\ul{
\li{Configure TLS 1.3 on nginx and Apache web servers}
\li{Implement TLS 1.3 in Python applications using the ssl module}
\li{Validate TLS configurations with openssl and testssl.sh}
\li{Understand TLS 1.3 cipher suites and key exchange mechanisms}
\li{Configure 0-RTT early data with appropriate protections}
\li{Disable legacy TLS versions (1.0, 1.1) and weak cipher suites}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Key Concepts}
\subtree{
\title{TLS 1.3 Cipher Suites}
\pre{\startverb
| Cipher Suite | Key Exchange | Authentication | Encryption | Hash |
|-------------|-------------|----------------|------------|------|
| TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384 | ECDHE/DHE | Certificate | AES-256-GCM | SHA-384 |
| TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256 | ECDHE/DHE | Certificate | AES-128-GCM | SHA-256 |
| TLS_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256 | ECDHE/DHE | Certificate | ChaCha20-Poly1305 | SHA-256 |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{TLS 1.3 vs 1.2 Improvements}
\ul{
\li{\strong{1-RTT Handshake}: Full handshake completes in one round trip (vs 2 in TLS 1.2)}
\li{\strong{0-RTT Resumption}: Resumed connections can send data immediately}
\li{\strong{No RSA Key Exchange}: Only ephemeral Diffie-Hellman (mandatory PFS)}
\li{\strong{Simplified Cipher Suites}: Removed CBC, RC4, 3DES, static RSA, SHA-1}
\li{\strong{Encrypted Handshake}: Server certificate is encrypted after ServerHello}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Key Exchange Groups}
\ul{
\li{\strong{x25519}: Curve25519 ECDH (preferred, fast)}
\li{\strong{secp256r1}: NIST P-256 ECDH (widely supported)}
\li{\strong{secp384r1}: NIST P-384 ECDH (higher security margin)}
\li{\strong{x448}: Curve448 ECDH (highest security)}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow}
\ol{
\li{Verify OpenSSL version supports TLS 1.3 (1.1.1+)}
\li{Generate or obtain TLS certificate and private key}
\li{Configure server to use TLS 1.3 cipher suites}
\li{Disable TLS 1.0 and 1.1 (optionally keep 1.2 for compatibility)}
\li{Set preferred key exchange groups}
\li{Enable OCSP stapling for certificate validation}
\li{Test configuration with openssl s_client and testssl.sh}
\li{Configure HSTS header for HTTP Strict Transport Security}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Security Considerations}
\ul{
\li{0-RTT data is vulnerable to replay attacks; limit to idempotent requests}
\li{Always include TLS 1.2 fallback if legacy client support is required}
\li{Use ECDSA certificates for better performance (vs RSA)}
\li{Enable OCSP stapling to improve client certificate validation}
\li{Set HSTS header with long max-age and includeSubDomains}
\li{Monitor for certificate transparency logs}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Validation Criteria}
\ul{
\li{[ ] TLS 1.3 handshake completes successfully}
\li{[ ] Only approved cipher suites are offered}
\li{[ ] Perfect forward secrecy is enforced}
\li{[ ] TLS 1.0 and 1.1 are rejected}
\li{[ ] OCSP stapling is functional}
\li{[ ] Certificate chain is valid and complete}
\li{[ ] testssl.sh reports no vulnerabilities}
}
}
}